ActsAsVideoFu
=============

Rails plugin that easily allows you to show video streams on your site. Currently, YouTube and Vimeo streams are supported.
#video_url is expected to be in these formats:

YouTube: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gEILFf2XSrM 
Vimeo: http://vimeo.com/726135

Example
=======

./script/generate scaffold Video title:string video_url:string

#video.rb
class Video < ActiveRecord::Base
  acts_as_video_fu
end


Video.create!(:title => "Some Title", :video_url => "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gEILFf2XSrM")


#show.html.erb
<%= display_video(@video) %>

# You can override the default video size by passing height & width
<%= display_video(@video, :height => 200, :width => 300) %>


